The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 900)

 The DVD of a BBC documentary on Luciano Pavarotti as he prepares for retirement after a glorious career. While touring the world for his final few performances, the 70-year-old tenor reflects on his life and times.

 THE SHOW

 (IIM Calcutta, February 13-15)

 Presented in association with The Telegraph, the three-day annual B-School fest at Joka features quiz, fashion show, rock music, choreography and drama contests. Jam, debate and literary events are also in the programme line-up.

 THE DISPLAY

 (CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm, from 3 pm on Mondays, till February 4)

 The solo show ? sub-titled the private world of Ganesh Pyne ? is the painter?s second major exhibition after his 1998 Retrospective.




